methods.name: public void onPayloadStarted(int cid) throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment: Called when the payload starts in the VM.

methods.name: public void onPayloadReady(int cid) throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment: Called when the payload in the VM is ready to serve.

methods.name: public void onPayloadFinished(int cid, int exitCode) throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment: Called when the payload has finished in the VM. `exitCode` is the exit code of the payload.

methods.name: public void onError(int cid, int errorCode, java.lang.String message) throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment: Called when an error occurs in the VM.

methods.name: public void onDied(int cid, int reason) throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment:
* Called when the VM dies.
     * 
     * Note that this will not be called if the VirtualizationService itself dies, so you should
     * also use `link_to_death` to handle that.
